ETEM Remediation Two LLC Rate Schedule FERC No. 1
Reactive Power and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
ETEM Remediation Two LLC (“ER2”) provides Reactive Power and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service (“Reactive Power”) from generating facilities located within the Allegheny Power Zone of the control area administered by the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This rate schedule sets forth ER2’s revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Power, as contemplated by the revised Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, filed in Docket No. ER00-3327-000, which provides that PJM will pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirement for Reactive Power.
This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
The total Reactive Power Annual Revenue Requirement is $ 1,600,000. The total monthly charge to PJM is $ 133,333.33.
Generating Facility Generating Unit Annual Revenue Requirement Monthly Revenue Requirement Pleasants 1 800,000 66,666.67 Pleasants 2 800,000 66,666.66
